Doctor Stories










New Technology Can Make Brain Surgery Safer
Stanford neurosurgeon Melanie Hayden, MD, discusses how genetic analysis and intraoperative MRI make brain tumor removal surgeries safer and more effective.




Our Patients
Delicate Brain Surgery Even More Difficult When a Tumor is Fist-sized
Mike Harris was so relieved to know that a brain tumor was behind his strange symptoms. Then came the hard part: Removing the fist-sized tumor.










For Patients







Stanford Health Care (formerly Stanford Hospital & Clinics) is known worldwide for the advanced patient care provided by its doctors and staff.  We also provide a wide range of guest services and amenities to our patients and visitors. Learn more about preparing for a hospital stay, billing and financial services, and our other support programs in Patients & Visitors.  




